import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude in the University District?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['lat'], ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average latitude of locations in the University District?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    return plt

chart = plot(data)
